                | Table size                | Icon size            |
                |---------------------------|----------------------|
                | small                     | extra small          |
                | medium                    | extra small          |
                | large                     | small                |

            - Only one column should be sorted at a time to allow screen readers to read the data accurately.
            - A column may only be sorted if all cells within it do not span multiple columns.
            - Add `.eds-table__column-header-cell--sortable` to table header cells `<th>` that are sortable.
            - To add a button directly into the header cell, use the CSS modifier class: `.eds-table__column-header-cell-sort-button`.
            - Import and connect the `sort-column` JavaScript (see <eds-link eds-href="?tab=code">Code</eds-link> tab) to add additonal functionality needed for a sortable Table.
            - See Accessibility section for additonal DOM requirements when creating a sortable Table.
