        ### Sort column
        `sort-column`: provides event listeners to notify an application when a sortable cell has been selected. This also updates Table classes and `aria-sort` within the Table.
        **This script does not provide the sorting functionality. Sorting should be done by your application.**

        To include this script, add the following to your application:
    {% endfilter %}

    {% filter markdown %}
        ### Usage Example:
    {% endfilter %}

    {% set example %}
        import { edsTableSortColumn } from '@xyz-ap153177/apex-kit';

        // the table <table> element
        let sortableTable = document.getElementById('sortableTableExample');
        let edsTableSortColumn = new edsTableSortColumn(sortableTable);

        // adds event listener to do things when a new sortable column is selected
        sortableTable.addEventListener('eds-table-sorted', (e) => {
            const activeSortedColumn = e.detail.el.innerText;
            const currentSortOrder = e.detail.sortOrder;

            document.getElementById('tableDocSiteSortableTableSRCaption').innerText = `Table sorted by '${activeSortedColumn}' in '${currentSortOrder}' order.`;
        });

        // function used to initiate the addition/removal of classes, attributes, etc. for the sortable cell
        function sortTable(e) {
            edsTableSortColumn.setActiveSort(e);
        }
    {% endset %}

    {{ library.eds_code_snippet(source=example, show_copy_button=false, language='javascript', hide_line_numbers=true)}}

    {% filter markdown %}
        ### Public methods:
        * `setActiveSort(newCell: HTMLTableCellElement)`: as a header to a sortable column is selected, this method is used to add/remove neccessary classes/attributes to change sorted columns. `newCell` must be a reference to the `<th>` element.
        * `getDefaultCaptionA11yText()`: gets the inital screen reader-only text for a caption.
        * `getSortButtonA11yText(headerCellText: string, sortOrder: string)`: returns default text for the `aria-label` of the button of a sortable header cell.
        * `getSortCaptionA11yText(headerCellText: string, sortOrder: string)`: returns default text for the screen reader-only text when sorting is enabled.
        * `getSortOrder(cell: HTMLElement)`: gets the current sort order of a sortable header cell.
        * `setSortableButtonAriaLabels()`: for every sortable column header, this adds `aria-label` attribute to the <eds-link eds-href="/components/button/button.html">Buttons</eds-link> within them if the respective column header does not have `aria-sort` set.
