            {% filter markdown %}
            ## Semantics
            - Mark all header cells with `<th>`.
            - Add `scope="row"` and/or `scope="col"` to all `<th>` elements.

            ## Form Controls in Table cells
            Header rows/columns provide a visual label and context to data within Table cells. When using <eds-link eds-href="/components/form/form.html">Form</eds-link> controls within Table cells, it's important to programmatically associate the form control to the header row/column to ensure context and relationship for assistive technologies. To add additional context to the <eds-link eds-href="/components/form/form.html">Form</eds-link> control, use one of the following:
            - Point to the IDs of row and column headers with `aria-labelledby`.
            - Clearly identify the context of the action with `aria-label`.

            ## Table captions
            The Table component doesn't use `<caption>` for captions because the horizontal scrollbar hides it. An accessible alternative way to add a caption:

            - Place the caption adjacent to the `<table>`.
            - Place the caption within a paragraph `<p>` with an `id`.
            - Add `aria-labelledby` to the `<table>` to reference to the caption's `id`.

            ## Fixed columns
            - When using fixed columns in your Table, the cells within a fixed column should not be a row header cell `<th scope="row">`. By using row header cells in a fixed column,
            NVDA+Firefox will not be able to navigate the fixed column properly.
            - When using fixed columns, designate the cells in the second column of each row into the `<th scope="row">` for the row.

            ## Sortable Tables
            - `aria-sort` should be put on column header cells `<th>` that are sortable (<eds-link eds-href="https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria-sort" eds-new-window>See valid aria-sort values</eds-link>).
            - Sortable column header cells `<th>` that are not currently sorted should use `aria-sort="none"`.
            - Sortable column header cells `<th>` should use a <eds-link eds-href="/components/button/button.html">Button</eds-link> within the cell to support keyboard-only sorting.
            - The following elements within the Table should have an additional `role` attribute:
                - `<table>` should have `role="table"`.
                - Column header cells `<th>` should have `role="columnheader"`.
                - Row header cells `<th>` should have `role="rowheader"`.
            - Use screen reader-only text within the caption of the Table to inform screen readers what column the Table is sorted by. Use `aria-live="polite"` on the screen reader-only text to inform users when a Table is sorted.
            - No more than one column can have an `aria-sort` attribute with a value other than "none" to allow screen readers to read the data accurately.

            ## Merged cells
            - When using merged cells to create complex Tables, handle cell association using `ids` and `headers` rather than just `scope`.
            - The number of cells in each row, including its `colspan` value, should be the same when using merged data cells.
            - Refer to the "Merged header cell" example on how to associate data cells to multiple row/column header cells.
